byline.original: By HELENE COOPER and ERIC SCHMITT

abstract: Defense Dept reports that Tunisian Islamic State militant Tariq bin al-Tahar bin al-Falih al-’Awni al-Harzi, 'person of interest' in 2012 attack on American consulate in Benghazi, Libya, was killed by American drone strike near Mosul, Iraq.
lead_paragraph: The Pentagon said that a “person of interest” in the 2012 attack in Benghazi, Libya, died in coordinated airstrikes in Mosul, Iraq, on June 15.

headline.main: U.S. Says Drone Killed an ISIS Member Linked to Benghazi Attack
headline.print_headline: U.S. Says Drone Killed an ISIS Operative
